oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Determining frequency of mortality by cause and association with days of age categories in a calf ranch
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Bigelow, R.A.
White, B.J.
Larson, R.L.
Lancaster, P.A.
Claxton, C.
Benoit, C.
Barnhardt, T.R.
Theurer, M.E.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: With the increase of beef-dairy calves, limited work has been done evaluating causes of mortality in commercial calf ranch­es. The objectives were to report the frequency of gross mortal­ity diagnosis by necropsy at commercial calf ranches and to de­termine association of days of age (DOA) with mortality.
